definitions.definition: A diadromous fish of species Lates calcarifer , of the Centropomidae family, order Perciformes , widely distributed in the Indo-West Pacific; a popular food fish.
Either of two fish, Scleropages leichardti and S. jardinii , of the family Osteoglossidae .
The fish Neoceratodus forsteri of the family Neoceratodontidae ; the Australian lungfish .

main_definition: A diadromous fish of species Lates calcarifer , of the Centropomidae family, order Perciformes , widely distributed in the Indo-West Pacific; a popular food fish.
